{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"fd644b28-9e3a-4854-b5de-b66c4391d4ef","content":"Here's what to change:\n\n1. **Update the adapter** – upgrade `NUnit3TestAdapter` to **v4.6.0+** (you're already there).\n\n2. **Add the platform package**:\n   ```xml\n   <PackageReference Include=\"Microsoft.Testing.Platform\" Version=\"1.5.3\" />\n   ```\n\n3. **Enable the new platform** in your `.csproj`:\n   ```xml\n   <PropertyGroup>\n     <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n   </PropertyGroup>\n   ```\n\n4. **Remove** `Microsoft.NET.Test.Sdk` — it's the VSTest entry point and is no longer needed (Microsoft.Testing.Platform replaces it).\n\n5. **Run tests** with:\n   ```bash\n   dotnet test\n   ```\n   Starting with .NET SDK 9.0.200+, `dotnet test` uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform when `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` is set. On older SDKs, use `dotnet run` or the generated test executable directly.\n\n6. **Optional** – if you use `runsettings`, review them; some VSTest-specific settings don't carry over.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8baae40e-1e1c-4bda-a9c3-ccbce56a4457","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating an NUnit test project from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform. This is a knowledge question - I don't need to look at any files. Let me provide a concise answer.","outputTokens":360},"id":"12d45fc8-1d03-4e12-971f-69a536cefaee","timestamp":"2026-04-07T14:20:47.494Z","parentId":"eadc83b2-8eee-45ba-b10c-a120da15f381"}
